The paper proposes a novel neural architecture for deep reinforcement learning, specifically for tackling the combinatorial increase of the number of possible actions with the number of action dimensions. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed agent on continuous control tasks, indicating a focus on Robotics (cs.RO) and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for image processing, suggesting a possible connection to Computer Vision (cs.CV).
